<div class="row">
	<div class="span8">
		<p>Established in 2006, the Family Sponsorship Program provides start-up costs to families to establish their own businesses and break the cycle of poverty.</p>

		<p>Director Mrisho Vuaa, a highly respected local Zanzibari, works with families to identify their skills, interests and abilities. He then provides training and ongoing mentorship to ensure the businesses are successful.</p>

		<p>Examples of businesses include:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>a produce stand which also sells kerosene and kangas (traditional women's garments)</li>
				<li>handmade soaps using island spices; sold to locals and tourist shops in Stone Town</li>
				<li>sale of daily caught fish; a fridge was purchased to keep fish fresh; sold to locals and area restaurants</li>
				<li>artisan breads; an oven was purchased; 80 loaves of bread which sell out daily</li>
				<li>milk and eggs; goats and chickens were purchased; sold to other villagers; also keeps owner families fed and healthy</li>
			</ul>
		<h4><strong><center>Your donation of $250 provides a family with the tools or inventory needed to establish a business and includes the training and mentoring necessary to ensure success.<center><strong></h4>

		<h4><strong><center>Your donation of $100 provides a family with a flock of chickens or a pair of goats.<center><strong></h4>
